2%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6877f8203d5881a51c1d7446%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221204%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EVirta%20Health%20CEO%20Sami%20Inkinen%20said%20the%20chronic%20care%20company%20has%20used%20generative%20AI%20to%20help%20boost%20its%20gross%20margins%20from%200%25%20to%2060%25.%3Cp%3EDrew%20Bird%20Photography%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EHealthcare%20startups%20increasingly%20want%20to%20use%20AI%20to%20care%20for%20more%20patients.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOthers%20are%20keeping%20the%20tech%20at%20arm's%20length%20over%20concerns%20about%20patient%20safety%20and%20experience.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHere's%20how%20startups%20are%20upping%20caseloads%2C%20boosting%20margins%2C%20and%20hitting%20profitability%20with%20AI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20growing%20number%20of%20healthcare%20startups%20are%20betting%20that%20artificial%20intelligence%20can%20help%20them%20do%20more%20with%20less%20%E2%80%94%20including%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20to%20care%20for%20more%20patients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20stakes%20are%20high%3A%20clinician%20shortages%2C%20tight%20margins%2C%20and%20mounting%20physician%20burnout%20are%20putting%20pressure%20on%20healthcare%20delivery%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStartups%20say%20AI%20could%20be%20the%20breakthrough%20that%20helps%20clinicians%20multiply%20their%20caseloads%20and%20earn%20extra%20cash%20without%20sacrificing%20care%20quality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20long-term%20vision%20is%20to%20continue%20to%20peel%20away%20aspects%20of%20in-person%20care%20and%20deliver%20the%20care%20itself%20via%20technology%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20CEO%20Daniel%20Perez%2C%20the%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20newly%20public%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpublic-hinge-health-wants-to-use-ai-care-delivery-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ephysical%20therapy%20company%20Hinge%20Health%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20a%20May%20interview%20with%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20some%20companies%20are%20leaning%20all%20the%20way%20in%20to%20automate%20more%20and%20more%20care%2C%20others%20are%20keeping%20the%20tech%20at%20arm's%20length%2C%20wary%20of%20the%20safety%20risks%20or%20the%20patient%20experience%20of%20turning%20clinician%20tasks%20over%20to%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20they're%20pushing%20AI%20behind%20the%20scenes%20to%20automate%20non-clinical%20tasks%20only.%20For%20some%2C%20that%20approach%20is%20offering%20a%20new%20lease%20on%20the%20startup's%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20allowing%20companies%20that%20historically%20would%20not%20have%20gotten%20to%20profitability%2C%20that%20may%20have%20had%20to%20go%20out%20of%20business%2C%20to%20sustain%20and%20to%20be%20able%20to%20keep%20driving%20impact%20long%20term%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20NOCD%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20Stephen%20Smith.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22151bc4f7-a7f0-412c-8df1-ae620ce1156c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMore%20patients%2C%20more%20money%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20healthcare's%20biggest%20AI%20moves%20are%20happening%20in%20musculoskeletal%20care%2C%20where%20companies%20like%20Hinge%20Health%20and%20Sword%20Health%20are%20aggressively%20using%20the%20tech%20to%20help%20make%20their%20physical%20therapists%20more%20efficient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESword%20Health%20spent%202024%20ramping%20up%20its%20AI%20applications%20for%20clinicians.%20While%20its%20physical%20therapists%20were%20expected%20to%20manage%20between%20200%20to%20300%20patients%20at%20a%20given%20time%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20year%2C%20the%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F3-billion-sword-health-cuts-physical-therapists-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewanted%20those%20providers%20to%20manage%20700%20patients%20at%20a%20time%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20average%20by%20the%20end%20of%202024%2C%20BI%20reported%20in%20November.%20Sword%20declined%20to%20comment%20for%20this%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESword's%20efforts%20toward%20that%20goal%20included%20using%20AI%20to%20pre-write%20messages%20for%20clinicians%20to%20send%20along%20to%20patients%2C%20per%20BI's%20reporting.%20The%20company%20also%20said%20at%20the%20time%20that%20its%20AI%20helped%20physical%20therapists%20prioritize%20patients%20who%20might%20need%20more%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHinge%20Health%20has%20taken%20a%20similar%20approach%20in%20implementing%20AI%2C%20including%20for%20patient-provider%20messaging.%20While%20Hinge%20Health%20declined%20to%20share%20its%20providers'%20caseloads%20for%20this%20story%2C%20the%20company%20says%20it's%20used%20AI%20to%20slash%2095%25%20of%20clinician%20hours%20spent%20on%20physical%20therapy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHinge%20Health%20also%20uses%20computer%20vision%20technology%20to%20guide%20patients%20through%20PT%20sessions%20at%20home.%20Following%20its%20May%20IPO%2C%20the%20company%20says%20it's%20actively%20working%20on%20more%20applications%20of%20AI%20to%20further%20automate%20care%20delivery%2C%20and%20has%20a%20large%20research%20and%20development%20team%20focused%20on%20that%20goal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20some%20point%2C%20whether%2010%2C%2050%2C%20or%20200%20years%20in%20the%20future%2C%20care%20delivery%20will%20be%20automated%20with%20technology.%20And%20that's%20a%20good%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20Hinge%20Health%20CEO%20Daniel%20Perez%20told%20BI%20in%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224480%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Daniel%20Perez%2C%20Co-Founder%20%26amp%3B%20CEO%20of%20Hinge%20Health%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6877f9ba3d5881a51c1d747a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223360%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDaniel%20Perez%2C%20Co-Founder%20%26amp%3B%20CEO%20of%20Hinge%20Health%3Cp%3EHinge%20Health%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EVirtual%20pediatric%20care%20startup%20Summer%20Health%20is%20also%20working%20to%20use%20AI%20to%20multiply%20the%20number%20of%20patients%20its%20providers%20can%20care%20for.%20While%20founder%20and%20CEO%20Ellen%20DaSilva%20doesn't%20think%20AI%20will%20replace%20doctors%2C%20she%20said%20the%20startup%20is%20working%20on%20automating%20some%20clinical%20tasks%20as%20well%20as%20administrative%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhereas%20a%20healthcare%20business%20with%20minimal%20technology%20implemented%20might%20expect%20providers%20to%20see%20five%20to%20seven%20patients%20an%20hour%2C%20Summer%20Health's%20largely%20text-messaging-based%20care%20model%20initially%20allowed%20its%20providers%20to%20see%20about%2010%20patients%20in%20an%20hour%2C%20DaSilva%20said.%20And%20with%20AI%2C%20%26quot%3Bthat%20number%20could%20pretty%20easily%20be%20doubled%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BOur%20providers%20still%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20room%20to%20run.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20could%20be%20especially%20good%20news%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-doctor-shortage-med-students-primary-care-family-medicine-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Especialties%20like%20pediatric%20care%20where%20there's%20a%20shortage%20of%20clinicians%3C%2Fa%3E.%20DaSilva%20said%20AI%20can%20help%20augment%20the%20remaining%20clinicians%20to%20help%20more%20patients%20get%20care%2C%20while%20hopefully%20reducing%20provider%20burnout%20along%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e0864486-ba2f-4305-9a45-0a6d8ffbf753%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBalancing%20operations%20and%20outcomes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20some%20healthcare%20startups%20go%20all%20in%20on%20AI%2C%20other%20companies%20aren't%20quite%20as%20sold%20on%20its%20potential%20for%20improving%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChronic%20care%20company%20Omada%20Health%2C%20which%20went%20public%20in%20May%2C%20has%20long%20used%20AI%20behind%20the%20scenes%2C%20like%20to%20suggest%20educational%20videos%20in%20Omada's%20content%20library%20for%20clinicians%20to%20send%20to%20their%20patients.%20But%20it's%20been%20slower%20to%20bring%20AI%20in%20front%20of%20patients%2C%20waiting%20until%20the%20company%20could%20point%20to%20significant%20LLM%20improvements%20and%20train%20the%20models%20on%20its%20own%20clinical%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20released%20its%20first%20patient-facing%20AI%20tool%20earlier%20in%20May%2C%20an%20AI%20agent%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexclusive-omada-health-ai-agent-nutrition-ipo-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eanswers%20members'%20nutrition%20questions.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20But%20Omada%20Health%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20Sean%20Duffy%20said%20the%20company%20has%20no%20intention%20of%20meaningfully%20replacing%20patient-provider%20interactions%20across%20its%20business%20with%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20yet%20to%20find%20someone%20who%20feels%20accountable%20to%20Chat%20GPT%2C%26quot%3B%20Duffy%20told%20BI%20in%20May%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fheres-who-got-rich-omada-healths-ipo-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOmada's%20IPO%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BI%20always%20quip%20that%20there's%20a%20reason%20that%20artificial%20intelligence%20is%20a%20buzzword%20and%20artificial%20empathy%20is%20not.%20You%20can%20expect%20us%20to%20always%20have%20a%20proactive%20people%20component.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOmada's%20diabetes%20care%20peer%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvirta-health-prescribing-ozempic-profitability-ipo-diabetes-startup-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EVirta%20Health%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20has%20been%20using%20machine%20learning%20since%202017%2C%20per%20founder%20and%20CEO%20Sami%20Inkinen.%20Between%202015%20and%202020%2C%20as%20Virta%20was%20figuring%20out%20how%20to%20use%20technology%20like%20machine%20learning%20to%20deliver%20better%20outcomes%2C%20it%20was%20turning%20a%20negative%20gross%20margin.%20But%20generative%20AI%20has%20helped%20the%20startup%20get%20that%20number%20in%20the%20green%3B%20today%20Virta%20boasts%20a%20roughly%2060%25%20gross%20margin%2C%20according%20to%20Inkinen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVirta%20has%20injected%20AI%20into%20many%20parts%20of%20its%20business%2C%20including%20into%20patient%20interactions%2C%20with%20AI-powered%20personalized%20care%20plans%20and%20chatbots%20available%20to%20help%20patients%20answer%20nutrition%20questions%2024%2F7.%20But%20Inkinen%20said%20AI%20isn't%20making%20clinical%20decisions%20and%20won't%20replace%20providers%20in%20Virta's%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20Virta%20doesn't%20have%20caseload%20targets%20for%20its%20providers%2C%20and%20said%20the%20company%20is%20rigidly%20focused%20on%20delivering%20better%20patient%20outcomes%20and%20improving%20its%20financials%20along%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sami%20Inkinen%2C%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Virta%20Health.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6877f9d03d5881a51c1d7483%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22750%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESami%20Inkinen%2C%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Virta%20Health.%3Cp%3EVirta%20Health%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMental%20health%20startup%20NOCD%20is%20using%20AI%20to%20tackle%20a%20broad%20range%20of%20administrative%20tasks%2C%20including%20clinical%20note%20dictation%20and%20revenue%20cycle%20management.%20CEO%20Stephen%20Smith%20said%20the%20tech%20has%20helped%20the%20company%20to%20reach%20profitability%2C%20allowing%20NOCD%20to%20grow%20its%20therapist%20network%20while%20keeping%20operating%20expenses%20low.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20startup%20does%20have%20a%20chatbot%20called%20Robin%20that%20therapists%20can%20ask%20for%20information%20during%20sessions.%20But%20that%20AI%20doesn't%20interact%20directly%20with%20patients%2C%20nor%20does%20it%20intervene%20unless%20the%20clinician%20seeks%20out%20its%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmith%20said%20he's%20treading%20carefully%20given%20the%20company's%20focus%20on%20patients%20with%20obsessive-compulsive%20disorder%2C%20which%20is%20typically%20classified%20as%20a%20serious%20mental%20illness.%20While%20NOCD%20may%20be%20able%20to%20increase%20its%20providers'%20caseloads%20with%20AI%20eventually%2C%20it's%20not%20a%20short-term%20goal%20for%20the%20company%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20these%20different%20projects%2C%20we%20know%20we%20have%20to%20proceed%20with%20some%20caution%20since%20we're%20dealing%20with%20a%20severe%20group%20of%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith%20said.%20%26quot%3BBringing%20AI%20to%20the%20clinical%20delivery%20of%20care%20is%20going%20to%20require%20a%20lot%20of%20research%2C%20largely%20because%20we%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20it's%20super%2C%20super%20effective%2C%20and%20that%20we%20can%20create%20a%20safe%20experience%20for%20our%20members%20and%20our%20therapists.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhealthcare-startups-using-ai-see-more-patients-chase-profits-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1752829202000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6877f7f5f748d8c055f5bca1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhealthcare-startups-using-ai-see-more-patients-chase-profits-2025-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Healthcare%20startups%20are%20betting%20that%20AI%20can%20help%20them%20do%20more%20with%20less%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0including%20in%20caring%20for%20patients.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22rtorrence%40businessinsider.com%20(Rebecca%20Torrence)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhealthcare-startups-using-ai-see-more-patients-chase-profits-2025-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Inside%20the%20AI%20boom%20that's%20changing%20how%20Big%20Law%20attorneys%20work%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20lawyer%20fixing%20his%20tie%20with%20a%20robot%20hand%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6876626185e81483682e0620%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBehind%20closed%20doors%20at%20Big%20Law%20firms%2C%20a%20technological%20shift%20is%20underway.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20legal%20profession%20is%20being%20overhauled%20as%20the%20top%20law%20firms%20are%20adopting%20AI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFive%20of%20the%2010%20largest%20US%20firms%20by%20revenue%20spoke%20to%20BI%20about%20how%20they're%20putting%20AI%20into%20practice.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThough%20each%20firm's%20process%20varies%2C%20they%20say%20they%20value%20testing%2C%20security%2C%20and%20review%20of%20new%20tools.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20largest%20law%20firms%20perform%20hand-painted%20legal%20work%20for%20the%20most%20demanding%20clients%20on%20the%20planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20same%20clients%20are%20now%20putting%20firms%20on%20the%20stand%2C%20asking%20whether%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flegal-tech-startups-raise-vc-funding-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eartificial%20intelligence%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20make%20their%20services%20better%2C%20faster%2C%20and%20cheaper%20(so%20long%20as%20it%20doesn't%20compromise%20their%20data).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BClients%20want%20it%20because%20they%20can%20see%20the%20potential%20client%20value%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ed%20Black%2C%20technology%20strategy%20leader%20for%20Ropes%20%26amp%3B%20Gray.%20%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20deliver.%20We're%20a%20service%20organization.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBehind%20closed%20doors%20at%20Big%20Law%20firms%2C%20a%20technological%20shift%20is%20underway.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-legaltech-fund-launches-law-firm-2-0-accelerator-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELawyers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20developers%2C%20and%20legal%20operations%20teams%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-lawyer-used-ai-help-win-case-clearbrief-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexperimenting%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20generative%20AI%20to%20reimagine%20everything%20from%20due%20diligence%20and%20document%20review%20to%20legal%20research%20and%20compliance%20risk%20detection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20lawyers%20at%20Morgan%20Lewis%20use%20legal%20tech%20to%20review%20fund%20documents%20and%20extract%20key%20terms%2C%20attorneys%20at%20DLA%20Piper%20rely%20on%20bespoke%20language%20models%20to%20help%20clients%20identify%20compliance%20risks.%20Gibson%20Dunn%20says%20it's%20piloting%20ChatGPT%20Enterprise%20with%20roughly%20500%20lawyers%20and%20staff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20understand%20how%20this%20transformation%20is%20playing%20out%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-lawyers-choosing-work-startups-instead-big-law-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elegal%20profession%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Business%20Insider%20contacted%20the%2010%20largest%20firms%20by%20revenue%2C%20according%20to%20American%20Lawyer%20Media's%20annual%20ranking.%20For%20each%2C%20we%20examined%20how%20it%20evaluates%20new%20AI%20tools%2C%20where%20it%20puts%20them%20to%20work%2C%20and%20how%20it%20governs%20their%20use%20so%20lawyers%20don't%20end%20up%20in%20headlines%20for%20the%20wrong%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFive%20of%20the%20top%2010%20firms%20provided%20partner-level%20interviews%20for%20this%20story.%20Representatives%20for%20Kirkland%20%26amp%3B%20Ellis%2C%20Latham%20%26amp%3B%20Watkins%2C%20Skadden%2C%20and%20White%20%26amp%3B%20Case%20declined%20to%20participate%2C%20and%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Baker%20McKenzie%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20an%20interview%20request.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDLA%20Piper%20rolls%20out%20Microsoft%20Copilot%20firmwide%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Signage%20is%20seen%20outside%20of%20the%20law%20firm%20DLA%20Piper%20in%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%20on%20August%2030%2C%202020.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F686fe0ff85e81483682dc2a5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Kelly%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAssess%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20DLA%20Piper%20has%20defended%20Microsoft%20in%20a%20defamation%20suit%20over%20AI-generated%20content%20and%20helped%20OpenAI%20put%20forward%20its%20views%20to%20Congress%20on%20how%20AI%20should%20be%20regulated.%20It's%20leaning%20into%20the%20tech%20internally%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDanny%20Tobey%2C%20chair%20of%20DLA%20Piper's%20AI%20and%20data%20analytics%20practice%2C%20said%20the%20firm%20has%20an%20internal%20group%20of%20lawyers%20and%20technologists%20who%20test%20tools%20and%20develop%20metrics%20for%20quality%20and%20accuracy.%20The%20team%20runs%20A%2FB%20tests%20on%20real%20cases%2C%20comparing%20results%20from%20traditional%20legal%20teams%20against%20AI-assisted%20ones%20to%20evaluate%20performance%20across%20speed%2C%20accuracy%2C%20and%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EApply%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Dc67d38262e4002218902b9f8cd7edce7cd2d3cc009cd7d236968b9095a8b136f%26postID%3D685b073768e21fcf0f184200%26postSlug%3Dbig-law-top-10-firms-ai-overhaul-use-cases-2025-7%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.microsoft.com%252Fen%252Fcustomers%252Fstory%252F19584-dla-piper-microsoft-365-copilot%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20highlighted%20DLA%20Piper%20as%20the%20first%20major%20law%20firm%20to%20adopt%20Copilot%20firmwide%2C%20after%20starting%20with%20several%20hundred%20licenses%20in%20late%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawyers%20use%20Copilot%20within%20their%20existing%20Microsoft%20365%20apps%2C%20Tobey%20said.%20Think%20drafting%20documents%2C%20poring%20over%20spreadsheets%2C%20and%20creating%20PowerPoint%20slides.%20For%20more%20advanced%20legal%20research%20and%20analysis%2C%20he%20said%2C%20attorneys%20turn%20to%20legal-specific%20tools%20like%20Harvey%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dlapiper.com%2Fen-us%2Fnews%2F2023%2F03%2Fdla-piper-to-utilize-cocounsel-the-groundbreaking-ai-legal-assistant-powered-by-openai-technology%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECoCounsel%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20LexisNexis%20Prot%C3%A9g%C3%A9.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDLA%20Piper%20has%20also%20developed%20custom%20language%20models%20to%20help%20clients%20spot%20compliance%20risks%20early%2C%20including%20under%20laws%20like%20the%20Foreign%20Corrupt%20Practices%20Act%20and%20the%20Anti-Kickback%20Statute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20found%20a%20number%20of%20issues%20before%20they%20metastasized%20into%20outright%20violations%2C%26quot%3B%20Tobey%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20that%20allowed%20the%20company%20to%20step%20in%20and%20do%20some%20education%20and%20compliance%20refreshing%20before%20there%20was%20a%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlign%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Tobey%20said%20the%20firm%20provides%20detailed%20training%20for%20lawyers%20on%20how%20to%20use%20its%20tools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20train%20on%20a%20per-tool%20basis%20because%20they%20all%20have%20strengths%20and%20weaknesses%2C%26quot%3B%20Tobey%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20were%20a%20doctor%2C%20you%20would%20not%20adopt%20a%20new%20tool%20without%20being%20trained%20in%20its%20limitations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EGibson%20Dunn%20pilots%20ChatGPT%20Enterprise%20with%20its%20lawyers%20and%20staff%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Signage%20is%20seen%20outside%20of%20the%20legal%20offices%20of%20the%20Gibson%20Dunn%20%26amp%3B%20Crutcher%20law%20firm%20in%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%2C%20on%20May%2010%2C%202021.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F686fe148f748d8c055f55c00%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Kelly%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAssess%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Before%20adopting%20any%20tool%2C%20Gibson%20Dunn%20runs%20a%20three-step%20review%20process%2C%20said%20Meredith%20Williams-Range%2C%20the%20firm's%20chief%20legal%20operations%20officer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETools%20must%20first%20pass%20an%20internal%20audit%20covering%20security%2C%20privacy%2C%20and%20risk.%20Next%2C%20they%20undergo%20proof-of-concept%20testing%20with%20a%20small%20group.%20Finally%2C%20tools%20must%20demonstrate%20real%20value%20to%20lawyers%20through%20hands-on%20use%2C%20a%20process%20that%20can%20take%20days%20or%2C%20as%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvey-legal-tech-startup-faces-growing-competition-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EHarvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20pilot%2C%20stretch%20over%20several%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EApply%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20ChatGPT%20Enterprise%20is%20one%20tool%20making%20its%20way%20through%20Gibson%20Dunn's%20internal%20processes.%20In%20June%2C%20the%20firm%20launched%20a%20pilot%20with%20more%20than%20500%20participants%20%E2%80%94%20a%20mix%20of%20lawyers%20and%20staff%20%E2%80%94%20to%20put%20the%20product%20through%20its%20paces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilliams-Range%20said%20she%20emailed%20practice%20group%20leaders%20and%20managing%20partners%20around%20the%20world%2C%20asking%20them%20to%20submit%20lawyers%20willing%20to%20test%20the%20tool.%20Three%20days%20later%2C%20450%20people%20had%20signed%20up%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%20twice%20what%20she%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGibson%20Dunn%20says%20it's%20also%20evaluating%20using%20rival%20AI%20models%20Google%20Gemini%20and%20Claude%20Enterprise.%20The%20firm%20works%20with%20a%20range%20of%20vendors%2C%20including%20Harvey%2C%20Thomson%20Reuters%2C%20and%20Microsoft.%20Some%20tools%2C%20like%20Harvey%20and%20CoCounsel%2C%20are%20used%20to%20support%20legal%20work%2C%20while%20Copilot%20helps%20with%20administrative%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20more%20specific%20use%20cases%2C%20the%20firm%20collaborates%20with%20developers%20to%20build%20custom%20workflows%20tailored%20to%20its%20practices%20and%20data%2C%20Williams-Range%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlign%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20firm's%20AI%20policy%20is%20reviewed%20quarterly%20to%20stay%20current%20with%20changing%20regulations%2C%20she%20said.%20It%20also%20includes%20a%20procurement%20playbook%20with%20specific%20terms%20around%20security%20and%20how%20it%20shares%20learnings%20about%20the%20tools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGibson%20Dunn%20also%20has%20a%20strategic%20advisory%20board%20made%20up%20of%20over%2030%20partners%20across%20offices%20globally.%20This%20brain%20trust%20meets%20monthly%20to%20guide%20policy%20decisions%2C%20debate%20use%20cases%2C%20and%20determine%20whether%20tools%20like%20ChatGPT%20Enterprise%20should%20be%20limited%2C%20expanded%2C%20or%20customized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJust%20because%20we%20can%20doesn't%20mean%20we%20should%2C%26quot%3B%20Williams-Range%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20principle%20that%20guides%20the%20board's%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESidley%20Austin%20hones%20prompt%20engineering%20skills%20during%20associate%20orientation%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Signage%20on%20display%20at%20Sidley%20Austin's%20office.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F687002eaf748d8c055f560f2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESidley%20Austin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAssess%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Over%20her%2029%20years%20with%20the%20firm%2C%20corporate%20lawyer%20Sharon%20Flanagan%20has%20watched%20Sidley%20embrace%20new%20tech%2C%20but%20with%20guardrails%20in%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20firm%20formed%20an%20AI%20council%20with%20members%20from%20its%20management%20committee%2C%20executive%20committee%2C%20and%20strategy%20team%20to%20set%20policies%20and%20identify%20use%20cases.%20Sidley%20typically%20starts%20with%20small-scale%20rollouts%20to%20pilot%20new%20tools%20before%20expanding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EApply%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Sidley%20has%20explored%20a%20range%20of%20AI%20tools%2C%20says%20Jane%20Rheem%2C%20Sidley's%20chief%20data%20and%20AI%20officer%20%E2%80%94%20from%20legal-specific%20platforms%2C%20to%20broader%20foundation%20models%2C%20to%20point%20solutions%20that%20help%20with%20timekeeping%20or%20narrative%20writing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20firm%20declined%20to%20identify%20the%20AI%20tools%20it's%20testing%2C%20saying%20it%20doesn't%20want%20to%20endorse%20products%20that%20may%20not%20be%20part%20of%20its%20long-term%20strategy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlanagan%20says%20uptake%20has%20been%20organic%20among%20litigators%20and%20corporate%20and%20regulatory%20attorneys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlign%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Implementation%20is%20only%20the%20beginning%2C%20Rheem%20says.%20The%20firm%20tracks%20usage%20after%20deployment%2C%20gathering%20data%20and%20feedback%20from%20%26quot%3Bsuperusers%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20early%20adopters%20who%20experiment%20broadly%20and%20flag%20where%20tools%20are%20working%20(or%20not).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESidley%20is%20also%20focused%20on%20making%20sure%20its%20youngest%20lawyers%20are%20fluent%20in%20the%20tools.%20This%20year%2C%20nearly%20300%20incoming%20associates%20participated%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sidley.com%2Fen%2Fnewslanding%2Fnewsannouncements%2F2025%2F01%2Fsidley-new-associates-compete-in-inaugural-generative-ai-hackathon-event%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egenerative%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20hackathon%20as%20part%20of%20their%20orientation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERopes%20%26amp%3B%20Gray%20uses%20AI%20tools%20like%20Harvey%20and%20Hebbia%20to%20squeeze%20more%20hours%20out%20of%20the%20day%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20logo%20of%20law%20firm%20Ropes%20%26amp%3B%20Gray%20LLP%20is%20seen%20outside%20of%20their%20office%20in%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%20on%20August%2031%2C%202020.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F686fe19a85e81483682dc2cc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Kelly%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAssess%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20When%20Ropes%20%26amp%3B%20Gray%20finds%20an%20AI%20service%20it%20likes%2C%20Ed%20Black%20and%20the%20IT%20and%20practice%20technology%20teams%20put%20on%20their%20investment%20banker%20hats.%20%26quot%3BWe%20phone%20them%20up%20every%20few%20weeks%20and%20say%2C%20'Tell%20us%20about%20your%20updates%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20Black%2C%20the%20firm's%20technology%20strategy%20leader.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20a%20tool%20can%20move%20to%20testing%2C%20it%20must%20pass%20a%20security%20and%20risk%20audit%3B%20only%20%26quot%3Bqualified%20vendors%26quot%3B%20make%20it%20to%20the%20next%20phase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20there%2C%20testing%20is%20twofold.%20First%2C%20a%20technical%20evaluation%20by%20the%20firm's%20technology%20team%20aims%20to%20ensure%20the%20product%20works%20as%20promised.%20Then%20a%20second%20round%20with%20lawyers%20examines%20usability%20and%20actual%20value%20in%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EApply%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Ropes%20%26amp%3B%20Gray%20rolled%20out%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flexisnexis-harvey-form-strategic-alliance-amid-growing-competition-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EHarvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20firmwide%20in%20June%2C%20after%20a%20year%20of%20use%20with%20a%20smaller%20test%20group%2C%20Black%20said.%20The%20firm%20has%20also%20collaborated%20with%20Harvey%20on%20a%20%26quot%3Bworkflow%20builder%26quot%3B%20that%20lets%20users%20design%20and%20deploy%20custom%20agents%20%E2%80%94%20software%20that%20can%20carry%20out%20tasks%20on%20its%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHebbia%2C%20an%20AI%20agent%20company%20focused%20on%20professional%20services%2C%20has%20proven%20particularly%20useful%20to%20lawyers%20like%20Melissa%20Bender%2C%20a%20partner%20in%20the%20asset%20management%20group%20and%20cohead%20of%20the%20private%20funds%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20institutional%20investors%20need%20fund%20documents%20reviewed%2C%20Bender%20uses%20Hebbia%20to%20extract%20key%20terms%20and%20speed%20up%20summaries.%20She%20estimates%20the%20process%20now%20takes%20two%20to%20three%20hours%2C%20less%20than%20what%20would%20typically%20be%20a%2010-hour%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlign%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Black%20stresses%20responsible%20use%20of%20the%20tools%2C%20starting%20with%20the%20principle%20that%20the%20results%20of%20using%20these%20tools%20are%20first%20drafts%2C%20not%20the%20final%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20private%20funds%20practice%20requires%20tool-specific%20training%20for%20junior%20and%20mid-level%20associates%2C%20Bender%20says%2C%20while%20more%20senior%20lawyers%20are%20%26quot%3Bstrongly%20encouraged%26quot%3B%20to%20take%20the%20training.%20The%20goal%20is%20to%20ensure%20lawyers%20know%20how%20to%20use%20the%20tools%20appropriately%20and%20empower%20them%20to%20speak%20with%20clients%20about%20the%20firm's%20technology%20capabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20in%20the%20business%20of%20selling%20legal%20services%2C%26quot%3B%20Bender%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20our%20associates%20to%20understand%20the%20differentiated%20nature%20of%20our%20offering.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMorgan%20Lewis%20requires%20staff%20to%20get%20credentialed%20before%20they%20can%20use%20the%20tools%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20logo%20of%20law%20firm%20Morgan%2C%20Lewis%20%26amp%3B%20Bockius%20LLP%20is%20seen%20on%20the%20exterior%20of%20its%20headquarters%20in%20Philadelphia%2C%20Pennsylvania.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F686fe0193d5881a51c1d1363%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20logo%20of%20law%20firm%20Morgan%2C%20Lewis%20%26amp%3B%20Bockius%20LLP%20is%20seen%20on%20the%20exterior%20of%20its%20headquarters%20in%20Philadelphia%20on%20September%201%2C%202020.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Kelly%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAssess%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20At%20Morgan%20Lewis%2C%20the%20first%20step%20in%20adopting%20AI%20isn't%20picking%20the%20tool.%20It's%20diagnosing%20the%20problem%2C%20said%20attorney%20Timothy%20Levin%2C%20who%20leads%20the%20firm's%20investment%20management%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnderstanding%20how%20legal%20work%20can%20be%20improved%20with%20AI%20is%20important%20to%20ensure%20tools%20are%20applied%20where%20they%20can%20have%20a%20real%20impact%2C%20rather%20than%20just%20throwing%20tech%20at%20a%20problem%2C%20Levin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20a%20tool%20passes%20security%20and%20risk%20checks%2C%20it's%20piloted%20by%20an%20attorney%20and%20C-suite%20advisory%20group%20spanning%2015%20practice%20areas%20and%20firm%20operations%20%E2%80%94%20a%20cross-section%20designed%20to%20vet%20the%20tool's%20value%20across%20the%20firm's%20legal%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EApply%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Morgan%20Lewis%20has%20been%20inundated%20with%20startup%20pitches%2C%20says%20Colleen%20Nihill%2C%20its%20chief%20AI%20and%20knowledge%20officer%2C%20as%20the%20legal%20tech%20gold%20rush%20draws%20a%20wave%20of%20new%20founders.%20To%20cut%20through%20the%20noise%2C%20Morgan%20Lewis%20favors%20larger%20enterprise%20partners%20that%20align%20with%20its%20technical%20standards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Thomson%20Reuters%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.morganlewis.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F12%2Fmorgan-lewis-and-thomson-reuters-enter-into-partnership-to-put-law-firms-needs-at-the-heart-of-ai-development%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estrategic%20partner%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20firm's%20advisory%20group%20meets%20regularly%20with%20Thomson%20Reuters%20to%20review%20existing%20tools%2C%20preview%20the%20product%20road%20map%2C%20and%20beta%20test%20unreleased%20features.%20They%20also%20collaborate%20to%20co-develop%20tools%20tailored%20to%20Morgan%20Lewis's%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20use%20case%20at%20Morgan%20Lewis%20involves%20reviewing%20fund%20documents%20for%20institutional%20investors%2C%20where%20CoCounsel%20Core%20helps%20attorneys%20summarize%20key%20terms%20and%20flag%20client-specific%20dealbreakers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlign%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Nihill%20said%20the%20firm%20requires%20its%20staff%20to%20get%20credentialed%20for%20tools%20before%20they%20can%20use%20them.%20Partners%20and%20firm%20leadership%20were%20the%20first%20to%20get%20CoCounsel%20Core-certified%2C%20a%20process%20that%20included%20Coursera-based%20coursework%2C%20hands-on%20exercises%2C%20and%20a%20final%20assessment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20certified%2C%20users%20receive%20a%20digital%20badge%20displayed%20on%20their%20internal%20profiles.%20Nihill%20says%20this%20signals%20to%20associates%20that%20these%20tools%20aren't%20just%20approved%3B%20they're%20a%20professional%20priority%20for%20the%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-law-top-10-firms-ai-overhaul-use-cases-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1752829202000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6876626185e81483682e0620%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-law-top-10-firms-ai-overhaul-use-cases-2025-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Big%20Law%20tells%20BI%20exactly%20how%20AI%20is%20